         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Offshore platform fabrication (OSY) for the MOG project</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="34514800"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Fabrication of the Offshore SwitchYard (OSY) Platform for the Modular Offshore Grid (MOG) project including but not limited to: procurement (partly), construction, load-out, hook-up and commissioning of the OSY Platform.</P>
               <P>Main project schedule: Fabrication Topside during 2018 and beginning of 2019, Fabrication Jacket during 2018, Installation of Jacket and Piles by the end of 2018, Installation of Topside in first half of 2019.</P>
               <P>The final contracting entity may be:</P>
               <P>(i) Elia Asset NV and/or Elia System Operator NV; and/or</P>
               <P>(ii) any company belonging to the Elia group; and/or</P>
               <P>(iii) a new company that will be set up by 1 of the of the companies of the Elia Group.</P>
               <P>More information, if selected, will be given in the Invitation to Tender (ITT). The selection procedure to qualify for this tender is described in the Pre-Qualification Questionnaire (PQQ).</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45255120"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45262420"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45262424"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45255410"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="45262425"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="BE"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Additional information on the MOG project via the following link: http://www.elia.be/~/media/files/Elia/PressReleases/2017/20170413_Elia-set-to-invest-in-an-electricity-plug-in-the-North-sea.pdf</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The OSY Fabrication Contractor's scope of work for the Topside includes, but not limited to:</P>
                  <P>— procure (partly) / assemble / fabricate / complete / commission the Topside structure,</P>
                  <P>— load-out Topside on cargobarge and seafasten accordingly,</P>
                  <P>— ballasting the cargobarge prior sail (tow condition),</P>
                  <P>— certification of fabricator’s workscope,</P>
                  <P>— offshore hook-up and commissioning (including transfers / logistics etc.).</P>
                  <P>The OSY Fabrication Contractor's scope of work for the Jacket includes, but not limited to:</P>
                  <P>— procure (partly) / assemble Jacket structure,</P>
                  <P>— load-out Jacket and Piles on cargobarge and seafasten accordingly,</P>
                  <P>— ballasting the cargobarge prior sail (tow condition),</P>
                  <P>— certification of fabricator’s workscope.</P>
                  <P>The procurement of the Main Steel and some Utilities as well as the Jacket and Topside Installation do not fall within the Platform Fabricator's scope.</P>
                  <P>This tender is open for countries within the European Economic Area (EEA) and countries which have signed and ratified a GPA agreement or a similar agreement / treaty with the EU.</P>
                  <P>Further specifications will be given in the Invitation to Tender (ITT); the ITT is only issued to candidates that are selected in the pre-qualification phase of the tender as is specified in the PQQ.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>This tender is open for countries within the European Economic Area (EEA) and countries which have signed and ratified a GPA agreement or a similar agreement / treaty with the EU.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
